Onkar Rai navigated by Gavin Lawrence in his Kabras Sugar Racing Skoda Fabia will be the first driver off the ramp during the RSC Athi Rally on Saturday, staring 7am Competitors will be flagged away from the Stoni Athi Resort and will finish at the same point in the afternoon in time for the prize giving scheduled for 5:30pm. Championship leader Baldev Charger driving his Mitsubishi Evolution will follow Onkar and Manvir Baryan will be third on the road in his Multiple Racing Team Skoda Fabia. Only three points separate Chager in his Kabras Sugar sponsored Mitsubishi Evolution X from Carl “Flash” Tundo who will be at the controls of his Top Fry Mitsubishi Evolution X. The championship contenders will be driving on the limit through Kunkur, Konza and Machakos ranch in a bid to win and earn vital points. The battle in the navigator championship is even more intense with both Ravi Soni and Tim Jessop on 53 points. Tuta Mionka is in third place in a Menengai Cream Subaru Impreza N12 with a score of 30 points. Bearing in mind that Ravi Soni navigates for Baldev Chager and Tim Jessop for Flash Tundo, rally fans are guaranteed an action packed day. The current warm weather indicates that the route will be muddy in some places, but the roads will be passable and dust free. Presentation of awards will take place at 5:30pm before the service crews and spectators return to Nairobi. Click here for more political news